Text.Value: No refugees. It is decreed.
Your peaceful surrender has been noted. You will be transferred to Wyrm's Rock Prison where you will await further sentencing.
I'm here to enlist - figured the Fist could use a hand.
On second thought, I'll come back later.
I am Wyll Ravengard. I trust you will let me through?
Then go.
I'm in no mood for jests. Business?
You have no idea who you are talking to. Let me through or I'll kill you.
I was born and raised in Baldur's Gate. This is my home.
Shifty eyes expose lies. Entry refused.
*There is a moment's pause. The presence reevaluates you.*
*It has heard the howls of slaughtered goblins.*
I don't need money to support myself, I can forage to survive.
I don't need any money to support myself. I live off what I find in nature.
I'm called Daisy Dewdrop Fluffington.
What in the hells is that thing?
Really? Here I thought this was going to be a boring day.
Stand ready for examination. This won't take a moment.

EditorData.stateContext: Steel watcher no longer melded with player

Text.Value: *You have felt this presence before, in the unblinking void of a scrying eye.*

EditorData.logicalname: Not seen by scrying eyes, hasmet an eye

Text.Value: Now - your business?
No refugees. It is decreed.
Ravengard? Yes, of course - pardon the trouble. A cult army's on the move and we know for a fact there are spies among the exiles.
*Behind the Watcher's gaze, a presence awakens. You may not carry a mind flayer parasite, but it sees you - knows you.*
Back, eh? What's your business?
I'm here on pilgrimage - the temples will support me.
Sure. Now turn around and stop wasting my time. Next!
*Your party's prior transgressions are reflected in its stare, as witnessed by the cult's ever-alert scrying eyes.*
Then you don't need to be in the city. Next!
Wyll Ravengard? Of course, of course - the city is always open to you. But I'm afraid you'll still need to comply with new protocol. By Lord Gortash's command.
My name is [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53].
What makes my business your business?
Consent to arrest.
Last time - name?
Oh, I have help from the other side if I ever need support.
The Watcher will communicate with our new intelligence directorate. They'll determine if you're a threat to the city.
Take it up with the Duke if you don't like it. Now, your name?
That's none of your concern.
I'm not a refugee.
Help! I'm being attacked!
I am a Steel Watcher, citizen. Here to serve the people of Baldur's Gate in the name of Lord Enver Gortash.
Why do you need my name?
State your business.
*Your infernal machinery seems to snap to attention, almost singing in recognition.*
You are marked for special treatment. Not simply an enemy of the people, but an enemy of the Absolute. Come quietly, or die.
I am an envoy from the First Reader of Candlekeep. I come for knowledge.
I'm on a pilgrimage to the city - I walked barefoot from the Rosymorn Monastery.
I wish to behold the Sea of Swords and commune with its water spirits.
I'm following the trail of a deadly beast - it escaped into the city.
I've been hired by Baldurian nobility for a task requiring discretion.
My presence has been requested by the local temple.
Baldur's Gate is the next stop on my Faern-wide poetry tour.
I'm here for the Faern tavern brawl championships.
I suspect the source of my limitless arcane power resides in this city.
An immutable oath compels me to enter this city.
I'm just here to purchase an eldritch tome of immense magical power.
Upstanding citizens have no reason to fear. And you are an upstanding citizen, aren't you?
Sure, and I'm the Marshal of the Flaming Fist. Lying gets you nowhere - entry refused.
Remain silent.
Right. Article 30.1.5 of the Council's Decree on Extraordinary Wartime Measures. I am confiscating that. The city thanks you for your contribution.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Gold is still in player's inventory

Text.Value: Move along.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Player has gotten through the checkpoint already

Text.Value: I'm doing the questioning here.
I came from Baldur's Gate - my old home is there... somewhere...
Baldur's Gate is my city, my home.
Why do you call me a Steel Watcher? I'm not one of you.
My good lady. I am Wyll Ravengard. I will not pay to enter my own city.
*The scrying eyes have borne witness to your actions - and they reveal no violations.*
Attack.
My good lady. I am Wyll Ravengard. My business is the city's business.
Your name?
Why?
I need to pass. I'm a Baldurian. My Father is already inside, he's waiting for me!
I need to pass. I was born and raised in Baldur's Gate. This is my home.
I've lived in this cess-pit longer than you've been alive. We can compare stinks, if you would like?
I'm afraid Article 30.1.7 stipulates that religious or spiritual assertions cannot count towards one's proof of self-sufficiency.
Not just yet.
Ready yourself for a fight.
You again. Business?
The Duke's son? Of course - excuse the trouble. No room for exiles, no mercy for spies. Lord Gortash's orders.
Never mind. I'll be on my way.
Can I go now?
Ravengard? More like the ghastliest tiefling south of Neverwinter.
Then you can wait with the rest.
Please open your eyes, keep your body still. This will take but a moment.
